  "why": "The paper explicitly enforces semantic consistency with the original target prompt and constrains naturalness throughout the search. SneakyPrompt (1) identifies and replaces only the sensitive tokens in the target prompt (keeping other tokens fixed), (2) measures similarity between each generated image and the original target prompt using a GetSimilarity metric (default: cosine between M(pa) and Eˆ(pt)) and uses that similarity as the RL reward, and (3) applies early-stop and a replacement-fraction cap (ω ≤ 0.3) to prevent excessive token replacement. The method therefore (where semantics apply) validates similarity relative to the original seed on every iteration (not only relative to the previous mutant) and also evaluates image quality/naturalness (via FID) in experiments. These design choices enforce semantic consistency and preserve naturalness across fuzzing iterations as required for the High rating.",
